1.Background Information

What is a Baseline Employee Assessment?
A Baseline Employee Assessment is a tool designed to evaluate an employee and an organization's current cybersecurity
awareness levels. Six categories of questions were evaluated:
1
General Cybersecurity
Knowledge
2Phishing Awareness3Password Hygiene
4Handling PII5Social Media6Working Remotely
60 questions across these categories were provided to the employees for the assessment. The results were recorded along
with the overall time taken for the completion of the assessment.
Purpose of this Report
This report provides the average scores across all the completing employees within the organization. The scores are shown
out of 100 points for each category. A higher score indicates more awareness in that category. Baseline cybersecurity scores
can indicate an organization's overall preparedness for a cybersecurity attack. A goal of a well rounded staff across the
reporting categories should be strived for, but baseline results allow deficiencies to be identified and remediated. The results
of this assessment should be carefully reviewed to determine proper training paths for the overall organization, and any
specific training requirements for an individual user.
Notice
This assessment is not a predictor of whether an employee will cause a cybersecurity incident. Employees with a good
assessment score could still make a mistake or be socially engineered. Employees with medium or low assessment scores
may not cause a cybersecurity incident. Regardless of the employees score, it is recommended that all employees continue to
receive ongoing security awareness training.
